value.0: A simple barmaid, looking a bit tired from the strain of continuing to serve customers while the world apparently ends outside.
Mercenaries are typically cold and distant, and this elf is no exception. He looks like he has seen many battles for any number of causes.

~ Trade of Blades menu ~

The Special: Deep Fried Flounder 2 Ducal Pieces
Caught this morning and fried to a crisp, served with a warm Skull Ale and Tartar Sauce, this succulent fish is sure to feed hungry mercenaries!

Catch of the Year: Broiled Spicy Greenfish 5 Ducal Pieces
A Neverwintan favorite! Locally farmed, our broiled Greenfish is seasoned with herbs and spices imported directly from Highcliff. Those halflings sure do have the best ingredients to make your tounge dance and your nostrils flare! Served with warm Skull Ale and a green salad. Tartar sauce available on request.

Seafood Platter 10 Ducal Pieces
Three helpings of Greenfish, two slabs of Deep Fried Flounder, 13 jumbo Shrimp, the Neverwintan Crabcakes, all the Skull Ale you can drink, and a slice of lemon for only 10 gold pieces! It's a steal!

Skull Ale 1 Ducal Piece
Try the most famous local drink for a single gold piece! Not responsible for picked pockets and lost items as you throw up your Greenfish and Flounder into the Sea.

Merchant Tills
In Nordock Rogue and Bard characters may attempt to use Slight of Hand to steal a few coins from a vendor's purse. Simply click on this object and follow the conversation. However no reward comes without risk so note that there is a small chance of getting caught each time you try and as an illegal act if caught you face potential jail time from the guards. But a canny escape artist should be out in no time. Characters wishing to become more proficient at this should train in picking pockets. Success can only be met at each till once per reset and if discovered you cannot attempt on the same till again that reset.
